    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Can You Read This?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Lynch letter thanks Book Review for increasing type size of best-seller lists (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks for changing your best-seller-list format (July 23) -- specifically, the type size -- so that the lists (as well as And Bear in Mind and New &amp; Noteworthy Paperbacks) have become a bunch of tiny ants crawling on the page. Or so they appear to my less-than-perfect trifocalized eyeballs.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thanks for changing your best-seller-list format (July 23) -- specifically, the type size -- so that the lists (as well as And Bear in Mind and New &amp; Noteworthy Paperbacks) have become a bunch of tiny ants crawling on the page. Or so they appear to my less-than-perfect trifocalized eyeballs.</p>
        <p>Way to go, Book Review: whack, whack, take that, aging America!</p>
        <p>Robert Lynch  Berkeley, Calif.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
